24/11/2010
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The defence ministry announced on Tuesday (November 23rd) that three soldiers died and another three were wounded during shooting drills involving live ammunition. It happened at the Cincu firing range in central Romania. According to the statement, the soldiers were killed by a shell that exploded before clearing a weapon's barrel. An investigation is under way. (AP, Hotnews.ro, Realitatea - 23/11/10)
